<subSubSection id="D0FE75E4F017C3587FDDB811C8757BC3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B608FE559DA50EB066DDC1D1CE0C95A0" pageNumber="755">Diagnosis A large, spectacularly distinct species whose major has a huge spherical head, proportionately reduced clypeus and mandibles, a mesonotum that drops vertically in side view to the metanotum, and a near-absence of pilosity on the head and mesosoma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
